208
00:10:16,705 --> 00:10:19,566
skipped one. You can also use animation layers and

209
00:10:19,606 --> 00:10:21,586
state graph to create new animations quickly.

210
00:10:22,867 --> 00:10:24,708
And speaking of state graphs, use them.

211
00:10:25,369 --> 00:10:27,531
Being able to set up and integrate your own animations

212
00:10:27,631 --> 00:10:30,553
is so powerful and allows you to get your things in the game

213
00:10:30,593 --> 00:10:31,914
faster and test them yourself.

214
00:10:32,535 --> 00:10:34,396
Waiting on engineering to integrate animations

215
00:10:34,476 --> 00:10:36,919
is frustrating and often just bottlenecks to the process.

216
00:10:37,779 --> 00:10:38,600
And about engineers.

217
00:10:39,800 --> 00:10:41,080
bug them for tools to help you.

218
00:10:41,681 --> 00:10:43,962
If you have an idea for a tool that will save you time,

219
00:10:44,382 --> 00:10:46,543
then talk to your lead or talk to engineering directly

220
00:10:46,603 --> 00:10:47,144
if you can.

221
00:10:47,904 --> 00:10:49,505
Often something that will take them an hour

222
00:10:49,545 --> 00:10:51,226
will save you days worth of frustration.

223
00:10:51,806 --> 00:10:52,987
Your time is important too,

224
00:10:53,427 --> 00:10:55,348
so work with your team to make your job easier.

225
00:10:55,909 --> 00:10:56,909
And speaking of your team,

226
00:10:57,489 --> 00:11:00,211
when somebody comes at you with an unrealistic request

227
00:11:00,231 --> 00:11:02,452
that'll blow out your schedule, push back.

228
00:11:02,892 --> 00:11:03,973
You're a team member too,

229
00:11:04,754 --> 00:11:06,434
and your time and opinion is important.

230
00:11:06,995 --> 00:11:08,855
Offer solutions and find a middle ground that's

231
00:11:08,895 --> 00:11:11,156
appropriate for your timeline and your team size.

232
00:11:11,896 --> 00:11:13,997
And if you know you have a difficult task before you,

233
00:11:14,237 --> 00:11:14,817
don't panic.

234
00:11:15,317 --> 00:11:17,358
Make a realistic plan and execute.

235
00:11:17,798 --> 00:11:19,178
Go in with a clear creative vision

236
00:11:19,238 --> 00:11:21,099
and identify, prioritize, and focus

237
00:11:21,159 --> 00:11:23,700
on what's most meaningful for the game and the player.

238
00:11:24,260 --> 00:11:26,100
If you've achieved that, then that's a success,

239
00:11:26,381 --> 00:11:28,441
